;; SKK-JISYO.godan - godan / ichidan verb 終止形 & 連体形 direct entries
;;
;; Rationale: SKK-JISYO.L stores godan verbs under okuri-ari keys
;; (e.g. `かw /変/代/交/替/買/換/飼/` for the ワ行 class), which the
;; runtime only recovers via bunsetsu.cpp:SplitMecab's isInflected branch.
;; That branch fires only when MeCab tags the reading as 動詞/形容詞.
;; UniDic-Lite mis-parses standalone terminal forms like `かう`,`はしる`,
;; `やむ` as 助詞+助動詞 or 名詞, so the recovery never triggers and typing
;; `kau` yields raw kana. The E2E report at
;; docs/e2e-kanji-katakana-report-2026-07-02.md:22,122-123,340 records
;; BUG-7/8 for this class of gap, annotated:
;;   「助詞『か』『った』との衝突。将来 `kau→買う` の SKK 追加で対応可」
;;
;; This file is the SKK-add fix. Loaded BEFORE SKK-JISYO.L.utf8 in
;; skkdictionary.cpp so the curated verb candidate lands at the head of
;; each reading's slot; the main dict's noun/name candidates (斯う, 蛙,
;; 龍, 松, 汁, ...) then push_back to the tail, keeping every existing
;; entry reachable but no longer topping the list.
;;
;; Multiple kanji per reading are ordered by modern frequency. Only
;; verbs whose 終止形 is a genuine modern-Japanese word are listed —
;; archaic 下二段 like 変う/替う/換う are excluded, which is why we can't
;; auto-synthesize from `かw` and need this hand-curated list.
;;
;; Scope: godan 終止形 = 連体形 (both `<stem>う/く/ぐ/す/つ/ぬ/ぶ/む/る`)
;; plus common 一段 動詞 (also `<stem>る`). Past-tense / continuative /
;; imperative are NOT added here — those are already covered by
;; SplitMecab's isInflected branch for MeCab-recognized surface forms.

